1. J Transcult Nurs. 2018 Apr 1:1043659618771142. doi: 10.1177/1043659618771142.[Epub ahead of print]Fear of Recurrence in Turkish Breast Cancer Survivors: A Qualitative Study.Şengün İnan F(1), Üstün B(2).Author information: (1)1 Dokuz Eylül University, İzmir, Turkey.(2)2 Üsküdar University, İstanbul, Turkey.PURPOSE: Fear of recurrence (FOR) of cancer is a distressing symptom and cannegatively affect breast cancer survivors' quality of life and psychologicalwell-being. The purpose of this qualitative study was to explore Turkish breastcancer survivors' experiences related to FOR.DESIGN: The data were collected through semistructured interviews, which wereconducted with 12 breast cancer survivors.RESULTS: The data were categorized into four themes: the quality of fear,triggers, effects on life, and coping. FOR survivors' lives in multiple aspects, and the women found it difficult to manage their fear.IMPLICATIONS: Nurses should be aware of FOR in survivors during follow-up care.In addition, it is essential to consider the impact of FOR on life, and survivorsshould be referred to appropriate resources and support services.DOI: 10.1177/1043659618771142 PMID: 29708040 